                'title' => 'Strawberry Jam',
                'slug' => 'strawberry-jam',
                'content' => 'This recipe for homemade strawberry jam will taste like you wouldn’t believe! Try it with Sousou; we guarantee you that your kids will fall in love with it!',
                'time' => '60',
                'serve' => '10',
                'video' => '',
                'directions' => '[{"direction":"Cut the strawberries into pieces.","_id":"5ae979969120d97d53a15ccb"},{"direction":"Place the strawberries in a big bowl. Then, cover them with the powdered sugar and pour the lemon juice over them.","_id":"5ae979969120d97d53a15cca"},{"direction":"Cover the bowl and keep in the fridge overnight so that the juices are released.","_id":"5ae979969120d97d53a15cc9"},{"direction":"The next day, wash 3 jars and pour boiling water over them. Turn them onto a towel to dry.","_id":"5ae979969120d97d53a15cc8"},{"direction":"Drain the strawberries in a strainer and collect the juice. Pour the juice into a big pot.","_id":"5ae979969120d97d53a15cc7"},{"direction":"Place the pot on the stove and let the juice boil for 10 minutes. Take the foam off with a skimmer every time foam appears.","_id":"5ae979969120d97d53a15cc6"},{"direction":"Add the strawberries and continue to cook for 20 minutes.","_id":"5ae979969120d97d53a15cc5"},{"direction":"Place one spoonful into a plate and put it in the fridge for 15 minutes. Take it out, wait 1 minute then tilt the plate and verify if the jam is cooked. If it slides, continue cooking for 5 more minutes.","_id":"5ae979969120d97d53a15cc4"},{"direction":"Using a ladle, pour the hot jam into the jars. Clean the edges and close the jars. Turn them upside down and leave until cool.","_id":"5ae979969120d97d53a15cc3"},{"direction":"","_id":"5ae979969120d97d53a15cc2"},{"direction":"2 jars","_id":"5ae979969120d97d53a15cc1"}]',
                'ingredients' => '[{"name":"strawberries","quantity":"1     Kilo","subIngredients":"","_id":"5ae979969120d97d53a15cce"},{"name":"powdered sugar","quantity":"750    Grams","subIngredients":"","_id":"5ae979969120d97d53a15ccd"},{"name":"Lemon, Juiced","quantity":"1","subIngredients":"","_id":"5ae979969120d97d53a15ccc"}]',
                'directions_legacy' => '<ul>
<li>Cut the strawberries into pieces.</li>
<li>Place the strawberries in a big bowl. Then, cover them with the powdered sugar and pour the lemon juice over them.</li>
<li>Cover the bowl and keep in the fridge overnight so that the juices are released.</li>
<li>The next day, wash 3 jars and pour boiling water over them. Turn them onto a towel to dry.</li>
<li>Drain the strawberries in a strainer and collect the juice. Pour the juice into a big pot.</li>
<li>Place the pot on the stove and let the juice boil for 10 minutes. Take the foam off with a skimmer every time foam appears.</li>
<li>Add the strawberries and continue to cook for 20 minutes.</li>
<li>Place one spoonful into a plate and put it in the fridge for 15 minutes. Take it out, wait 1 minute then tilt the plate and verify if the jam is cooked. If it slides, continue cooking for 5 more minutes.</li>
<li>Using a ladle, pour the hot jam into the jars. Clean the edges and close the jars. Turn them upside down and leave until cool.</li>
<li>2 jars.</li>
</ul>',
                'ingredients_legacy' => '<ul>
<li>1 Kilo strawberries</li>
<li>750g powdered sugar</li>
<li>1 Lemon, juiced</li>
</ul>',
