                'directions_legacy' => '<ul>
<li>Dough</li>
<li></li>
<li>In a bowl, place the flour, salt, &amp; melted butter. Add water. Knead well using your hands to form a dough. Cover with nylon film. Leave for half an hour.</li>
<li>Roll out the dough and place it into a tart tray.</li>
<li>Bake it in the oven until golden.</li>
<li></li>
<li>Filling</li>
<li></li>
<li>In a pan, fry the onions with oil and keep aside.</li>
<li>In a bowl, combine the Roquefort, mozzarella and feta cheese. Add the onion and the fresh oregano and mix well.</li>
<li>Spread the mixture onto the dough.</li>
<li>Beat the eggs with a fork and add the fresh cream, black pepper and salt. Spread this mixture over the tart, then sprinkle the Gruyere cheese.</li>
<li>Bake in a moderate oven until the cheese melts.</li>
</ul>',
