                'directions_legacy' => 'Stew:

&nbsp;
<ul>
<li>In a pan on the stove, fry the onions and garlic with oil until light golden. Then, add the chicken and fry them. Next, add the potatoes salt, pepper and cinnamon stick.</li>
<li>Add the tomato paste. Cover with water and cook. Reduce the heat when it starts boiling. Let it simmer for half an hour until the chicken is cooked.</li>
</ul>
Rice:

&nbsp;
<ul>
<li>Soak the two types of rice in water for half an hour before cooking.</li>
<li>In a pan, fry the vermicelli until golden; then, add the rice and water.</li>
<li>Once it starts boiling, reduce the heat and cook the rice until all water evaporates.</li>
<li>Serve the rice with the stew.</li>
</ul>',
                'ingredients_legacy' => '<ul>
<li>4 Chicken legs cut into 8 pieces</li>
<li>3 Chicken breasts cut into 12 pieces</li>
<li>1 Big onion, diced</li>
<li>6 Cloves garlic, smashed</li>
<li>5 Medium potatoes cut into big cubes</li>
<li>Salt to taste</li>
<li>2 Tablespoons tomato paste</li>
<li>1 Stick cinnamon</li>
<li>2 Tablespoons corn oil</li>
</ul>
Rice:
<ul>
<li>½ Cup Egyptian rice</li>
<li>½ Cup Uncle Benz rice</li>
<li>½ Cup vermicelli</li>
<li>1 ¾ Cups water</li>
<li>Salt to taste</li>
</ul>',
