                'title' => 'Mars Cheese Cake',
                'slug' => 'mars-cheese-cake',
                'content' => 'Be a little creative and prepare a special cheesecake with the delicious Mars bars. It’s creamy, sweet and a must try.',
                'time' => '30',
                'serve' => '10',
                'video' => '',
                'directions' => '[{"direction":"Crush the biscuits in the blender. Mix them with the melted butter. Press the mixture over the base and sides of a cheesecake pan. Put in the fridge for 30 minutes.","_id":"5a9e73559120f32ca1e50c33"},{"direction":"Mix gelatin powder with hot water until dissolved. Stand to cool.","_id":"5a9e73559120f32ca1e50c32"},{"direction":"Beat cream cheese with white sugar with an electric mixer. Stir in the gelatin mix with the chopped Mars bars.","_id":"5a9e73559120f32ca1e50c31"},{"direction":"In a separate bowl, beat 240 ml of the fresh cream until soft peak forms and add them to cheese mixture.","_id":"5a9e73559120f32ca1e50c30"},{"direction":"Combine brown sugar, extra butter and 60 ml fresh cream in a saucepan. Stir over low heat until you have a caramel sauce.","_id":"5a9e73559120f32ca1e50c2f"},{"direction":"Melt the chocolate and 60 ml fresh cream in the microwave for 1 minute.","_id":"5a9e73559120f32ca1e50c2e"},{"direction":"Pour half of the cheese mixture over the refrigerated biscuit. Drizzle half of the caramel and chocolate sauces over the cheese mixture. Using a barbecue skewer, create the marbling effect by pulling it forward and backward.","_id":"5a9e73559120f32ca1e50c2d"},{"direction":"Repeat the process with remaining cheese mixture and sauces.","_id":"5a9e73559120f32ca1e50c2c"},{"direction":"Cover cheesecake and refrigerate for 4 hours.","_id":"5a9e73559120f32ca1e50c2b"}]',
                'ingredients' => '[{"name":"plain chocolate biscuits","quantity":"400 Grams","subIngredients":"","_id":"5a9e73559120f32ca1e50c3e"},{"name":"butter, melted","quantity":"220    Grams","subIngredients":"","_id":"5a9e73559120f32ca1e50c3d"},{"name":"brown sugar","quantity":"4 Tablespoons","subIngredients":"","_id":"5a9e73559120f32ca1e50c3c"},{"name":"extra butter","quantity":"40    Grams","subIngredients":"","_id":"5a9e73559120f32ca1e50c3b"},{"name":"fresh cream","quantity":"360    ml","subIngredients":"","_id":"5a9e73559120f32ca1e50c3a"},{"name":"milk chocolate","quantity":"100    Grams","subIngredients":"","_id":"5a9e73559120f32ca1e50c39"},{"name":"gelatin powder","quantity":"3    Teaspoons","subIngredients":"","_id":"5a9e73559120f32ca1e50c38"},{"name":"water","quantity":"60    ml","subIngredients":"","_id":"5a9e73559120f32ca1e50c37"},{"name":"cream cheese","quantity":"500    Grams","subIngredients":"","_id":"5a9e73559120f32ca1e50c36"},{"name":"white sugar","quantity":"110    Grams","subIngredients":"","_id":"5a9e73559120f32ca1e50c35"},{"name":"Mars bars, chopped","quantity":"4","subIngredients":"","_id":"5a9e73559120f32ca1e50c34"}]',
                'directions_legacy' => '<ul>
<li>Crush the biscuits in the blender. Mix them with the melted butter. Press the mixture over the base and sides of a cheesecake pan. Put in the fridge for 30 minutes.</li>
<li>Mix gelatin powder with hot water until dissolved. Stand to cool.</li>
<li>Beat cream cheese with white sugar with an electric mixer. Stir in the gelatin mix with the chopped Mars bars.</li>
<li>In a separate bowl, beat 240 ml of the fresh cream until soft peak forms and add them to cheese mixture.</li>
<li>Combine brown sugar, extra butter and 60 ml fresh cream in a saucepan. Stir over low heat until you have a caramel sauce.</li>
<li>Melt the chocolate and 60 ml fresh cream in the microwave for 1 minute.</li>
<li>Pour half of the cheese mixture over the refrigerated biscuit. Drizzle half of the caramel and chocolate sauces over the cheese mixture. Using a barbecue skewer, create the marbling effect by pulling it forward and backward.</li>
<li>Repeat the process with remaining cheese mixture and sauces.</li>
<li>Cover cheesecake and refrigerate for 4 hours.</li>
</ul>',
                'ingredients_legacy' => '<ul>
<li>400 Grams plain chocolate biscuits</li>
