                'title' => 'Stuffed Kibbeh with Eggplants',
                'slug' => 'stuffed-kibbeh-with-eggplants',
                'content' => 'Kibbeh and eggplants sound weird together? Well not really. Try Sousou’s special recipe loaded with flavor to indulge your taste buds with every bite.',
                'time' => '40',
                'serve' => '6',
                'video' => '',
                'directions' => '[{"direction":"FILLING","_id":"5a9808541312c87072664d5d"},{"direction":"Peel the eggplant and cut it into small cubes.","_id":"5a9808541312c87072664d5c"},{"direction":"Fry the eggplant using 3 tablespoons of oil. Then, put them in a strainer.","_id":"5a9808541312c87072664d5b"},{"direction":"Fry the onion with one tablespoon of oil until it changes color. Add salt, pepper and red pepper.","_id":"5a9808541312c87072664d5a"},{"direction":"Next, add the pomegranate molasses.","_id":"5a9808541312c87072664d59"},{"direction":"Mix the onion mixture with the eggplants well.","_id":"5a9808541312c87072664d58"},{"direction":"","_id":"5a9808541312c87072664d57"},{"direction":"KIBBEH DOUGH","_id":"5a9808541312c87072664d56"},{"direction":"Wash the cracked wheat and let them sit for 15 minutes.","_id":"5a9808541312c87072664d55"},{"direction":"In a food processor, mash the onion. Then, add the cracked wheat and mash for 5 minutes. Next, add the meat and mash for another 5 minutes.","_id":"5a9808541312c87072664d54"},{"direction":"Remove the mixture and knead it with wet hands to make the kibbeh.","_id":"5a9808541312c87072664d53"},{"direction":"","_id":"5a9808541312c87072664d52"},{"direction":"KIBBEH","_id":"5a9808541312c87072664d51"},{"direction":"Divide the kibbeh preparation into small balls","_id":"5a9808541312c87072664d50"},{"direction":"Make a hole in the middle of each ball, then, enlarge it using your finger; bring together the sides and sharpen the edges of the kibbeh.","_id":"5a9808541312c87072664d4f"},{"direction":"Once all dough is done, deep fry the kibbeh in one cup of corn oil.","_id":"5a9808541312c87072664d4e"},{"direction":"Cut each kibbeh in 2 pieces on long and fill each with some of the eggplant mixture.","_id":"5a9808541312c87072664d4d"},{"direction":"Decorate each one with pomegranate seeds.","_id":"5a9808541312c87072664d4c"}]',
            'ingredients' => '[{"name":"FILLING","quantity":"bold","subIngredients":"","_id":"5a9808541312c87072664d6b"},{"name":"Medium round eggplant","quantity":"1","subIngredients":"","_id":"5a9808541312c87072664d6a"},{"name":"Onion peeled & diced","quantity":"1","subIngredients":"","_id":"5a9808541312c87072664d69"},{"name":"corn oil","quantity":"4         Tablespoons","subIngredients":"","_id":"5a9808541312c87072664d68"},{"name":"Salt and pepper and red pepper to taste","quantity":"","subIngredients":"","_id":"5a9808541312c87072664d67"},{"name":"pomegranate molasses","quantity":"1         Teaspoon","subIngredients":"","_id":"5a9808541312c87072664d66"},{"name":"Pomegranate seeds (for decoration)","quantity":"1 cup","subIngredients":"","_id":"5a9808541312c87072664d65"},{"name":"","quantity":"","subIngredients":"","_id":"5a9808541312c87072664d64"},{"name":"KIBBEH DOUGH","quantity":"bold","subIngredients":"","_id":"5a9808541312c87072664d63"},{"name":"ground  meat  (beef or lamb)","quantity":"300    Grams","subIngredients":"","_id":"5a9808541312c87072664d62"},{"name":"fine cracked wheat (burghol)","quantity":"1        Cup","subIngredients":"","_id":"5a9808541312c87072664d61"},{"name":"Big onion peeled","quantity":"1","subIngredients":"","_id":"5a9808541312c87072664d60"},{"name":"Salt and pepper to taste","quantity":"","subIngredients":"","_id":"5a9808541312c87072664d5f"},{"name":"marjoram","quantity":"1         Teaspoon","subIngredients":"","_id":"5a9808541312c87072664d5e"}]',
                'directions_legacy' => 'Filling:

&nbsp;
<ul>
<li>Peel the eggplant and cut it into small cubes.</li>
<li>Fry the eggplant using 3 tablespoons of oil. Then, put them in a strainer.</li>
<li>Fry the onion with one tablespoon of oil until it changes color. Add salt, pepper and red pepper.</li>
<li>Next, add the pomegranate molasses.</li>
<li>Mix the onion mixture with the eggplants well.</li>
</ul>
&nbsp;

Kibbeh dough:

&nbsp;
<ul>
<li>Wash the cracked wheat and let them sit for 15 minutes.</li>
<li>In a food processor, mash the onion. Then, add the cracked wheat and mash for 5 minutes. Next, add the meat and mash for another 5 minutes.</li>
<li>Remove the mixture and knead it with wet hands to make the kibbeh.</li>
</ul>
&nbsp;

Kibbeh:

&nbsp;
<ul>
<li>Divide the kibbeh preparation into small balls.</li>
<li>Make a hole in the middle of each ball, then, enlarge it using your finger; bring together the sides and sharpen the edges of the kibbeh.</li>
<li>Once all dough is done, deep fry the kibbeh in one cup of corn oil.</li>
<li>Cut each kibbeh in 2 pieces on long and fill each with some of the eggplant mixture.</li>
<li>Decorate each one with pomegranate seeds.</li>
</ul>',
                'ingredients_legacy' => 'Filling:

&nbsp;
<ul>
<li>1 Medium round eggplant</li>
<li>1 Onion peeled &amp; diced</li>
<li>4 Tablespoons corn oil</li>
<li>Salt and pepper and red pepper to taste</li>
<li>1 Teaspoon pomegranate molasses</li>
<li>1 Cup pomegranate seeds (for decoration)</li>
</ul>
Kibbeh dough:

&nbsp;
<ul>
<li>300g Ground meat (beef or lamb)</li>
<li>1 Cup fine cracked wheat (burghol)</li>
<li>1 Big onion peeled</li>
<li>Salt and pepper to taste</li>
<li>1 Teaspoon marjoram</li>
</ul>',
