                'directions_legacy' => 'Meat:

&nbsp;
<ul>
<li>Grind the onions, garlic and green pepper.</li>
<li>Mix all the ingredients in one bowl.</li>
</ul>
&nbsp;

Dough:

&nbsp;
<ul>
<li>Mix in a bowl the flour, yeast, salt, sugar and oil. Then, add the egg. Gradually, add the water and knead to form a firm dough.</li>
<li>Put the dough on a floured work surface. Knead until smooth for about 15 minutes. If the dough is too stiff, add some water.</li>
<li>Divide the dough into 4 balls. Cover and let it rest for 2 hours. Shape each dough to form small balls of an apricot size.</li>
<li>Roll out each ball of dough very thin and add some of the meat mixture. Place them in a tray near each other and bake in oven until they change color.</li>
</ul>',
                'ingredients_legacy' => 'Meat:

