er and salt to taste","quantity":"","subIngredients":"","_id":"5a3a4951a760f001b6cdcf95"},{"name":"Parmesan cheese","quantity":"3      Tablesp","subIngredients":"","_id":"5a3a4951a760f001b6cdcf94"}]',
                'directions_legacy' => 'Crepes:

&nbsp;
<ul>
<li>In a bowl, mix the eggs, salt and vanilla with a fork. Then, add the flour and gradually add the milk.</li>
<li>Heat a lightly oiled pan over medium heat. Pour the batter using a small ladle. Tilt the pan in a circular motion so the batter coats the surface evenly</li>
<li>Cook the crepe for about 2 minutes, until the bottom is light brown. Then, flip it. Cook the other side.</li>
</ul>
&nbsp;

White sauce:

&nbsp;
<ul>
<li>Mix all the ingredients and stir over low heat until the sauce thickens.</li>
</ul>
&nbsp;

Spinach filling:

&nbsp;
<ul>
<li>In a bowl, mix the spinach, turkey ham, cheese and Mushrooms with the white sauce.</li>
<li>Fill each crepe with the spinach mix. Roll it and Put it in the Pyrex. Repeat until the Pyrex is full.</li>
<li>Bake for 15 minutes and set aside.</li>
<li>Before serving, mix the fresh cream, mustard and white pepper and pour it over the crepes. Sprinkle with parmesan cheese and some almonds Bake until golden.</li>
</ul>',
                'ingredients_legacy' => 'Crepes:

&nbsp;
<ul>
<li>1 ½ Cups flour</li>
<li>1 Cup milk</li>
<li>1 Tablespoon mazola oil</li>
<li>2 Eggs</li>
<li>1 Pinch salt</li>
<li>1 Pinch vanilla</li>
</ul>
&nbsp;

White cream:

&nbsp;
<ul>
<li>1 Cup milk</li>
<li>1 Tablespoon flour</li>
<li>1 Tablespoon butter</li>
</ul>
&nbsp;

Spinach Filling:

&nbsp;
<ul>
<li>400g Frozen spinach</li>
<li>200g Chopped turkey ham</li>
<li>100g Grated gruyere cheese</li>
<li>200g Sliced mushrooms</li>
<li>600g Fresh cream</li>
<li>½ Tablespoon mustard</li>
<li>White pepper and salt to taste</li>
<li>3 Tablespoon parmesan cheese</li>
</ul>',
