                'content' => 'Enjoy another Lebanese treasure with Sousou! Learn how to prepare the pumpkin jazarieh, flavored with lemon and orange juice, and mixed with a variety of nuts. We are sure that no one would like to miss it!',
                'time' => '40',
                'serve' => '15',
                'video' => '',
                'directions' => '[{"direction":"Dissolve the limestone in 3 liters water in a large bowl. Leave for 2 hours. Filter the limestone with a fine cloth.","_id":"5a393653c359006b2e96f94a"},{"direction":"Wash, peel, slice and grate the pumpkins.","_id":"5a393653c359006b2e96f949"},{"direction":"Soak the pumpkins in limestone solution for 15 hours.","_id":"5a393653c359006b2e96f948"},{"direction":"Strain and wash well the grated pumpkin and leave to dry.","_id":"5a393653c359006b2e96f947"},{"direction":"Bring sugar and water to a boil in a non-stick pan. Stir constantly until the sugar is dissolved.","_id":"5a393653c359006b2e96f946"},{"direction":"Skim the frost from the surface.","_id":"5a393653c359006b2e96f945"},{"direction":"Add the grated pumpkin and the lemon juice to the syrup. Cook on low heat until the pumpkins are tender and the syrup thickened. Remove the grated pumpkin with a slotted spoon.","_id":"5a393653c359006b2e96f944"},{"direction":"Mix it with the walnuts, almonds and pine nuts.","_id":"5a393653c359006b2e96f943"},{"direction":"Spoon the hot jam in a jar. Close tightly the cap.","_id":"5a393653c359006b2e96f942"},{"direction":"Turn the jar up side down and leave until becomes cold.","_id":"5a393653c359006b2e96f941"}]',
                'ingredients' => '[{"name":"pumpkin","quantity":"1 kg","subIngredients":"","_id":"5a393653c359006b2e96f953"},{"name":"1 kilo","quantity":"sugar","subIngredients":"","_id":"5a393653c359006b2e96f952"},{"name":"water","quantity":"2 liters","subIngredients":"","_id":"5a393653c359006b2e96f951"},{"name":"tablespoons lemon juice","quantity":"3","subIngredients":"","_id":"5a393653c359006b2e96f950"},{"name":"peeled almond","quantity":"100 gram","subIngredients":"","_id":"5a393653c359006b2e96f94f"},{"name":"peeled walnuts","quantity":"100 gram","subIngredients":"","_id":"5a393653c359006b2e96f94e"},{"name":"pine nuts","quantity":"100 gram","subIngredients":"","_id":"5a393653c359006b2e96f94d"},{"name":"limestone","quantity":"100 gram","subIngredients":"","_id":"5a393653c359006b2e96f94c"},{"name":"water","quantity":"3 liters","subIngredients":"","_id":"5a393653c359006b2e96f94b"}]',
                'directions_legacy' => '<ul>
<li>Dissolve the limestone in 3 liters water in a large bowl. Leave for 2 hours. Filter the limestone with a fine cloth.</li>
<li>Wash, peel, slice and grate the pumpkins.</li>
<li>Soak the pumpkins in limestone solution for 15 hours.</li>
<li>Strain and wash well the grated pumpkin and leave to dry.</li>
<li>Bring sugar and water to a boil in a non-stick pan. Stir constantly until the sugar is dissolved.</li>
<li>Skim the frost from the surface.</li>
<li>Add the grated pumpkin and the lemon juice to the syrup. Cook on low heat until the pumpkins are tender and the syrup thickened. Remove the grated pumpkin with a slotted spoon.</li>
<li>Mix it with the walnuts, almonds and pine nuts.</li>
<li>Spoon the hot jam in a jar. Close tightly the cap.</li>
<li>Turn the jar up side down and leave until becomes cold.</li>
</ul>',
                'ingredients_legacy' => '<ul>
