                'directions_legacy' => 'Orange Mouhallabieh:

&nbsp;
<ul>
<li>Combine the orange, tangerine and lemon juices with sugar and corn flour in a saucepan.</li>
<li>Place on the stove and stir until it thickens. Then, add the fresh cream</li>
<li>Pour the mixture in a Pyrex and place in the fridge.</li>
<li>Spread over the grated almonds.</li>
</ul>
&nbsp;

Milk Mouhallabieh:

&nbsp;
<ul>
<li>Combine the liquid milk with corn flour, sugar and musk in a saucepan.</li>
<li>Place on the stove and stir until it thickens. Add the orange blossom water.</li>
<li>Pour the mixture on the cooled orange mouhallabieh.</li>
<li>Let it cool in the fridge till next day.</li>
</ul>',
