                'directions_legacy' => 'Filling:

&nbsp;
<ul>
<li>Mix all ingredients together, and keep aside.</li>
</ul>
&nbsp;

Dough:

&nbsp;
<ul>
<li>Combine the flour, salt and sugar in a bowl. Make a hole in the center, and pour in the instant yeast. Then, add the oil and gradually add the water and kneed it to form the dough.</li>
<li>Put the dough on a floured work surface. Knead it, until it becomes smooth.</li>
<li>Divide the dough into 4 balls. Cover with a nylon film and cloth. Leave it to rest for 1 hour.</li>
</ul>
&nbsp;

Fatayer:

&nbsp;
<ul>
<li>Roll out the dough on a floured table until it becomes thin. Cut it with a rounded cookie cutter, in order to create circles.</li>
<li>In each circle, add one tablespoon of the cheese mixture. Join the two sides together making sure to press firmly and keep open in the middle.</li>
<li>Put them onto an oiled tray.</li>
<li>Bake them in the oven until golden brown.</li>
<li>30 pieces</li>
</ul>',
