                'directions_legacy' => '<ul>
<li>Rub the chicken pieces with oil, salt and pepper; Place them in the Pyrex. Then, bake them in the oven until golden brown. Set aside.</li>
<li>Fry the onions and strain them. Repeat the same procedure for the carrots, peppers and mushrooms.</li>
<li>Place in one pan the onions, carrot, mushrooms and water, add the cube Maggi and vinegar. Cook for 15 minutes.</li>
</ul>
&nbsp;

Sauce:

&nbsp;
<ul>
<li>In a separate bowl, combine the corn flour, soy sauce and brown sugar. Then, add ½ cup of water. Next, add salt and ginger and mix well. Then, add them to the mixture of onions and peppers.</li>
<li>Lastly add the chicken and let simmer for 20 minutes or until the sauce thickens.</li>
</ul>
&nbsp;

Rice:

&nbsp;
<ul>
<li>Boil Basmati rice.</li>
<li>On the stove, fry the three types of pepper and add them to the boiled rice. Then, add salt.</li>
<li>Decorate the plate with fried cashew nuts.</li>
</ul>',
                'ingredients_legacy' => '<ul>
<li>10 Chicken legs (boneless)</li>
<li>2 Chicken breasts, cut into quarters</li>
<li>1 Sweet green pepper cut into big cubes</li>
<li>1 Sweet yellow pepper cut into big cubes</li>
<li>1 Sweet red pepper cut into big cubes</li>
<li>3 Medium onions, thinly sliced</li>
<li>3 Carrots, cut round</li>
<li>1 Big can of mushrooms, sliced</li>
<li>½ Cup vinegar</li>
<li>1 Cube Magi dissolved in 1 cup of hot water</li>
<li>Salt and Pepper to taste</li>
</ul>
&nbsp;

Sauce:

&nbsp;
<ul>
<li>1 Tablespoon corn flour</li>
<li>½ Cup soy sauce</li>
<li>1 Tablespoon brown sugar</li>
<li>½ Cup of Water</li>
<li>½ Teaspoon fresh ginger</li>
<li>Salt to taste</li>
</ul>
&nbsp;

Rice:

&nbsp;
<ul>
<li>½ Sweet red pepper, cubed</li>
<li>½ Yellow pepper, cubed</li>
<li>½ Green pepper, cubed</li>
<li>1 Cup basmati rice</li>
<li>2 Tablespoons oil</li>
<li>2 Cups water</li>
<li>½ Cup fried cashew nuts</li>
</ul>',
