                'title' => 'Stuffed Mini Kibbeh with Labneh',
                'slug' => 'stuffed-mini-kibbeh-with-labneh',
                'content' => 'Sousou\'s Gourmet Kebbeh! These delicious labneh filled mini bites are a testament of her talent.',
                'time' => '60',
                'serve' => '10',
                'video' => '',
            'directions' => '[{"direction":"Combine the labneh with mint and oil and divide them into very small balls (size of a Kalamata olive). Set aside.","_id":"59c8f24ff385c430425129fd"},{"direction":"Wash the cracked wheat and leave it for 15 minutes. In a food processor, mash the onion then add the cracked wheat, mash for 5 minutes. Add the salt and pepper, then the meat and grind for another 5 minutes. Remove the mixture and knead it with wet hands to make the kibbeh dough.","_id":"59c8f24ff385c430425129fc"},{"direction":"Divide the kibbeh dough into small balls.","_id":"59c8f24ff385c430425129fb"},{"direction":"Take each ball, make a hole in the middle, and enlarge it with your finger; fill it with one ball of labneh. Close the kibbeh and roll it by hand to form a ball. Then, moisten with cold water. Place them in a tray.","_id":"59c8f24ff385c430425129fa"},{"direction":"Deep-fry the kibbeh in a pan with one cup of oil, until golden brown.","_id":"59c8f24ff385c430425129f9"},{"direction":"","_id":"59c8f24ff385c430425129f8"},{"direction":"Makes around 110 mini kibbeh.","_id":"59c8f24ff385c430425129f7"}]',
            'ingredients' => '[{"name":"STUFFING","quantity":"bold","subIngredients":"","_id":"59c8f24ff385c43042512a09"},{"name":"Goat Labneh","quantity":"200 Grams","subIngredients":"","_id":"59c8f24ff385c43042512a08"},{"name":"Chopped Mint","quantity":"\\u00bd    Cup","subIngredients":"","_id":"59c8f24ff385c43042512a07"},{"name":"Olive Oil","quantity":"1 Tablespoon","subIngredients":"","_id":"59c8f24ff385c43042512a06"},{"name":"","quantity":"","subIngredients":"","_id":"59c8f24ff385c43042512a05"},{"name":"KIBBEH DOUGH:","quantity":"bold","subIngredients":"","_id":"59c8f24ff385c43042512a04"},{"name":"Beef or Lamb ground  meat","quantity":"500 Grams","subIngredients":"","_id":"59c8f24ff385c43042512a03"},{"name":"Fine Cracked Wheat (Burghol)","quantity":"1\\u00be Cup","subIngredients":"","_id":"59c8f24ff385c43042512a02"},{"name":"Big Onion Peeled","quantity":"1","subIngredients":"","_id":"59c8f24ff385c43042512a01"},{"name":"Salt","quantity":"1 Teaspoon","subIngredients":"","_id":"59c8f24ff385c43042512a00"},{"name":"Black Pepper","quantity":"\\u00bc Teaspoon","subIngredients":"","_id":"59c8f24ff385c430425129ff"},{"name":"","quantity":"","subIngredients":"","_id":"59c8f24ff385c430425129fe"}]',
                'directions_legacy' => '<ul>
<li>Combine the labneh with mint and oil and divide them into very small balls (size of a Kalamata olive). Set aside.</li>
<li>Wash the cracked wheat and leave it for 15 minutes. In a food processor, mash the onion then add the cracked wheat, mash for 5 minutes. Add the salt and pepper, then the meat and grind for another 5 minutes. Remove the mixture and knead it with wet hands to make the kibbeh dough.</li>
<li>Divide the kibbeh dough into small balls.</li>
<li>Take each ball, make a hole in the middle, and enlarge it with your finger; fill it with one ball of labneh. Close the kibbeh and roll it by hand to form a ball. Then, moisten with cold water. Place them in a tray.</li>
<li>Deep-fry the kibbeh in a pan with one cup of oil, until golden brown.</li>
<li>Makes around 110 mini kibbeh.</li>
</ul>',
                'ingredients_legacy' => 'Stuffing:

