                'directions_legacy' => '<ul>
<li>Fry onion with oil until it changes color. Add garlic and mix for 5 minutes. Turn of the stove, then, add salt, black pepper, red pepper and basil.</li>
<li>Grind the pine nuts and almonds and add it to the basil mixture. Set aside.</li>
<li>Wash the cracked wheat and leave it for 15 minutes. In a food processor, mash the onions then; add the cracked wheat and mash for 5 more minutes. Add salt and Pepper, then, the meat for another 5 minutes. Remove the mixture and knead it with wet hands to make the kibbeh dough.</li>
<li>Divide the kibbeh into very small balls.</li>
<li>Take each ball, put it in the palm of your hand and using your fingers, make a flat rounded kibbeh; put some of the basil mixture in the shaped kibbeh dough. Then, make another rounded flat kibbeh. Cover the mixture and close it tightly. Moisten each Kibbeh with cold water and place them in a tray.</li>
<li>Deep-Fry the kibbeh in one cup of oil until golden brown.</li>
<li>Makes around 100 mini kibbeh.</li>
</ul>',
                'ingredients_legacy' => 'Filling;

