                'directions_legacy' => 'Filling:

&nbsp;
<ul>
<li>Fry the onions with oil until golden brown. Mix with salt, pepper, red pepper and parsley.</li>
<li>Grind the fried pine nuts and almonds and add them to the mixture.</li>
</ul>
&nbsp;

Kibbeh:

&nbsp;
<ul>
<li>Wash the cracked wheat and leave it for 15 minutes. In a food processor, mash the onion then add the cracked wheat and mash for 5 minutes. Add the meat and grind for another five minutes. Remove the mixture and knead it with wet hands to make the kibbeh.</li>
<li>Divide the kibbeh into very small balls. Make a hole in the middle of each ball, and enlarge it with your finger. Fill it with some of the onions mixture. Bring together the sides and sharpen the edges. Then, moisten with cold water. Place them in a tray.</li>
<li>Deep-Fry the mini kibbeh.</li>
<li>Makes around 80 mini kibbeh (size of an olive)</li>
</ul>',
                'ingredients_legacy' => 'Filling;

&nbsp;
<ul>
<li>9 Medium onions, diced</li>
<li>¾ Cup fried pine nuts</li>
<li>½ Cup fried almonds</li>
<li>¼ Cup chopped parsley</li>
<li>1 Teaspoon salt</li>
<li>½ Teaspoon black pepper</li>
<li>¼ Teaspoon red pepper</li>
<li>1 Tablespoon corn oil</li>
</ul>
&nbsp;

Kibbeh:

&nbsp;
<ul>
<li>300g Ground meat (beef or lamb)</li>
<li>¾ Cup Fine cracked wheat (burghol)</li>
<li>1 Big onion peeled</li>
<li>1 Teaspoon salt</li>
<li>¼ Teaspoon black pepper</li>
</ul>',
