                'directions_legacy' => 'Curry:

&nbsp;
<ul>
<li>Coat the chicken with oil, pepper, cinnamon &amp; salt. Bake the chicken in the oven until golden brown. Keep aside.</li>
<li>Fry the onions, peppers, coriander and garlic. Then, add the tomatoes, salt and pepper. Keep cooking until the tomatoes become soft. Next, add the mushrooms and the bag of the frozen vegetables. Cook for 20 minutes.</li>
<li>In a separate pot, stir the water &amp; magi cubes together. Then, add the flour, curry, tabasco and ketchup. Stir on low heat until the sauce thickens.</li>
<li>Add the sauce to the vegetables mixture. Cook for 10 minutes. Next, add the grated apples. Lastly, add the chicken.</li>
</ul>
&nbsp;

Rice:

&nbsp;
<ul>
<li>On the stove, fry the mushrooms and the mixed vegetables. Then, add the curry and Magi cubes. Next, add the rice and 5 cups of chicken stock. Once it starts boiling, reduce the heat &amp; cook the rice until all the water has evaporated.</li>
</ul>',
                'ingredients_legacy' => 'Curry:

