                'title' => 'Spinach Tart',
                'slug' => 'spinach-tart',
                'content' => 'Countless are the benefits of spinach and unfortunately it\'s so hard to convince kids with it. Here\'s your ultimate creative Sousou recipe to trick them into not leaving a crumb! Bake a tart out of it!',
                'time' => '40',
                'serve' => '8',
                'video' => '',
                'directions' => '[{"direction":"DOUGH:","_id":"59955a2f0cb50a705891d96e"},{"direction":"Place the flour, salt & melted Butter in a bowl. Add the water.  Kneed well using your hands until a dough is formed. Cover the dough with nylon film and let it rest for half an hour.","_id":"59955a2f0cb50a705891d96d"},{"direction":"Roll the dough out and place it into a tart pan.","_id":"59955a2f0cb50a705891d96c"},{"direction":"Bake it in the oven until it is golden brown.","_id":"59955a2f0cb50a705891d96b"},{"direction":"","_id":"59955a2f0cb50a705891d96a"},{"direction":"FILLING:","_id":"59955a2f0cb50a705891d969"},{"direction":"In a pan, fry the onions with oil. Then, add the spinach, mushrooms & Maggi cube.","_id":"59955a2f0cb50a705891d968"},{"direction":"Mix together on the stove until the spinach becomes soft. Set aside.","_id":"59955a2f0cb50a705891d967"},{"direction":"When the spinach mixture is cold, add the feta cheese.","_id":"59955a2f0cb50a705891d966"},{"direction":"Spread the mixture on the dough.","_id":"59955a2f0cb50a705891d965"},{"direction":"Beat the eggs, salt and white pepper with a fork. Then, add the fresh cream.","_id":"59955a2f0cb50a705891d964"},{"direction":"Spread the Egg over the spinach and place the gruyere cheese on top.","_id":"59955a2f0cb50a705891d963"},{"direction":"Bake in a moderate Oven heat until the cheese has melted and golden brown.","_id":"59955a2f0cb50a705891d962"}]',
                'ingredients' => '[{"name":"THE DOUGH","quantity":"bold","subIngredients":"","_id":"59955a2f0cb50a705891d982"},{"name":"Flour","quantity":"250 Grams","subIngredients":"","_id":"59955a2f0cb50a705891d981"},{"name":"Melted Butter","quantity":"125   Grams","subIngredients":"","_id":"59955a2f0cb50a705891d980"},{"name":"Salt","quantity":"1 Pinch","subIngredients":"","_id":"59955a2f0cb50a705891d97f"},{"name":"Water","quantity":"1\\/3  Cup","subIngredients":"","_id":"59955a2f0cb50a705891d97e"},{"name":"","quantity":"","subIngredients":"","_id":"59955a2f0cb50a705891d97d"},{"name":"THE FILLING","quantity":"bold","subIngredients":"","_id":"59955a2f0cb50a705891d97c"},{"name":"chopped Spinach","quantity":"1 Kilo","subIngredients":"","_id":"59955a2f0cb50a705891d97b"},{"name":"Onions, cut into small cubes","quantity":"3","subIngredients":"","_id":"59955a2f0cb50a705891d97a"},{"name":"Corn Oil","quantity":"2 Tablespoons","subIngredients":"","_id":"59955a2f0cb50a705891d979"},{"name":"fresh Mushrooms, sliced","quantity":"200 Grams","subIngredients":"","_id":"59955a2f0cb50a705891d978"},{"name":"Maggi vegetable stock cube","quantity":"1","subIngredients":"","_id":"59955a2f0cb50a705891d977"},{"name":"Feta Cheese, mashed","quantity":"200 Grams","subIngredients":"","_id":"59955a2f0cb50a705891d976"},{"name":"","quantity":"","subIngredients":"","_id":"59955a2f0cb50a705891d975"},{"name":"THE TOP LAYER","quantity":"bold","subIngredients":"","_id":"59955a2f0cb50a705891d974"},{"name":"Eggs","quantity":"2","subIngredients":"","_id":"59955a2f0cb50a705891d973"},{"name":"Fresh Cream","quantity":"200   Ml","subIngredients":"","_id":"59955a2f0cb50a705891d972"},{"name":"Salt to taste","quantity":"","subIngredients":"","_id":"59955a2f0cb50a705891d971"},{"name":"White Pepper","quantity":"\\u00bd  Teaspoon","subIngredients":"","_id":"59955a2f0cb50a705891d970"},{"name":"Gruyere Cheese","quantity":"200   Grams","subIngredients":"","_id":"59955a2f0cb50a705891d96f"}]',
                'directions_legacy' => 'Dough:

&nbsp;
<ul>
<li>Place the flour, salt &amp; melted Butter in a bowl. Add the water. Kneed well using your hands until a dough is formed. Cover the dough with nylon film and let it rest for half an hour.</li>
<li>Roll the dough out and place it into a tart pan.</li>
<li>Bake it in the oven until it is golden brown.</li>
</ul>
&nbsp;

Filling:

&nbsp;
<ul>
<li>In a pan, fry the onions with oil. Then, add the spinach, mushrooms &amp; Maggi cube.</li>
<li>Mix together on the stove until the spinach becomes soft. Set aside.</li>
<li>When the spinach mixture is cold, add the feta cheese.</li>
<li>Spread the mixture on the dough.</li>
<li>Beat the eggs, salt and white pepper with a fork. Then, add the fresh cream.</li>
<li>Spread the Egg over the spinach and place the gruyere cheese on top.</li>
<li>Bake in a moderate Oven heat until the cheese has melted and golden brown.</li>
</ul>',
                'ingredients_legacy' => 'The Dough:

&nbsp;
<ul>
<li>250 Grams flour</li>
<li>125 Grams melted butter</li>
<li>1 Pinch salt</li>
<li>1/3 Cup water</li>
</ul>
&nbsp;

The Filling:

&nbsp;
<ul>
<li>1 Kilo chopped spinach</li>
<li>3 Onions, cut into small cubes</li>
<li>2 Tablespoons corn oil</li>
<li>200 Grams fresh mushrooms, sliced</li>
<li>1 Maggi vegetable stock cube</li>
<li>200 Grams feta cheese, mashed</li>
</ul>
The Top Layer:
<ul>
<li>2 Eggs</li>
<li>200 ml Fresh cream</li>
<li>Salt to taste</li>
<li>½ Teaspoon white pepper</li>
<li>200 Grams gruyere cheese</li>
</ul>',
