45af6dffe4cf2f6e129"},{"name":"YOGHURT","quantity":"bold","subIngredients":"","_id":"5994445af6dffe4cf2f6e128"},{"name":"Yoghurt","quantity":"1 Kg","subIngredients":"","_id":"5994445af6dffe4cf2f6e127"},{"name":"Cloves garlic, smashed","quantity":"2","subIngredients":"","_id":"5994445af6dffe4cf2f6e126"},{"name":"Sumac to garnish","quantity":"3 Teaspoons","subIngredients":"","_id":"5994445af6dffe4cf2f6e125"}]',
                'directions_legacy' => 'Filling:

&nbsp;

Combine all the ingredients. Set aside

&nbsp;

Mante:

&nbsp;
<ul>
<li>Mix the flour with sugar and salt and then, add the olive oil. Next, add the water and knead to form a soft dough. Divide the dough into 4 parts. Cover with nylon paper and leave to rest for 1 hour.</li>
<li>Roll the dough until it becomes thin. Cut it with the smallest round cookie cutter in order to create a circle. Then, place ¼ teaspoon of filling into each round and fold it by pressing the edges together like a little boat.</li>
<li>Arrange the mante in a greased baking tray. Bake them in the oven until golden.</li>
</ul>
&nbsp;

Sauce:

&nbsp;
<ul>
<li>Melt the Maggi cubes with one cup of water, then add the tomato paste and red pepper and bring to a boil. Keep warm.</li>
</ul>
&nbsp;

Yoghurt:

&nbsp;
<ul>
<li>In a separate bowl, mix the yoghurt with garlic and salt.</li>
<li>Just before serving, heat the mante, pour the sauce over it and cover with a thick layer of yoghurt. Sprinkle some sumac on top.</li>
</ul>',
                'ingredients_legacy' => 'Filling:

&nbsp;
<ul>
<li>300 g Minced meat</li>
<li>3 Medium onions, finely chopped</li>
<li>1 Teaspoon sweet pepper</li>
<li>½ Teaspoon black pepper</li>
<li>¼ Teaspoon red pepper</li>
<li>Salt to taste</li>
</ul>
Dough:

&nbsp;
<ul>
<li>4 Cups flour</li>
<li>2 Tablespoons olive oil</li>
<li>¼ Teaspoon salt</li>
<li>¼ Teaspoon sugar</li>
<li>1 ¼ cup water</li>
</ul>
Sauce:

&nbsp;
<ul>
<li>1 Tablespoon tomato paste</li>
<li>2 Maggi cubes (chicken broth)</li>
<li>1 Cup water</li>
<li>Salt to taste</li>
</ul>
Yoghurt:

&nbsp;
<ul>
<li>1 Kg Yoghurt</li>
<li>2 Cloves garlic, smashed</li>
<li>3 Teaspoons sumac to garnish</li>
</ul>',
