                'directions_legacy' => 'Meat:

&nbsp;
<ul>
<li>Grind the onion &amp; parsley and add them to meat making sure to mix well. Then, add salt, pepper &amp; flour. Using your hands, take a small piece of meat and roll it into round balls. Place all the meatballs in a tray.</li>
<li>Bake in the oven for 15 to 20 minutes.</li>
</ul>
&nbsp;

Sauce:

&nbsp;
<ul>
<li>Fry the onions with oil in a pan, then, add the tomatoes and stir for 7 minutes. Next, add the water, pepper, salt &amp;cinnamon stick. Lastly add the tomato paste.</li>
<li>Cook on low heat for 15 minutes, then add the meatballs and continue to cook until the sauce thickens.</li>
</ul>
&nbsp;

Rice:

&nbsp;
<ul>
<li>Soak the two types of rice in water for half an hour before cooking.</li>
<li>Fry half a cup of vermicelli; add the rice, with water and salt.</li>
<li>Once it starts boiling, reduce the heat &amp; cook the rice until all the water evaporates.</li>
</ul>',
                'ingredients_legacy' => 'Meat;

