<li>Cover it with a tablecloth and keep it aside</li>
</ul>
&nbsp;

Filling:

&nbsp;
<ul>
<li>Place the butter and the dates in a tray and put it in the oven until the butter has melted. Then, grind the remaining ingredients in a food processor.</li>
</ul>
&nbsp;

Maamoul Mad with Dates:

&nbsp;
<ul>
<li>In a buttered tray, place half of the dough, making sure it is well moistened. Then place the dates mixture on top of the dough, piece by piece and flatten it out using your hand.</li>
<li>Continue the same procedure until you create a layer of dates covering the bottom layer of dough.</li>
<li>Put the remaining dough on top of the dates layer and moisten the top well.</li>
<li>Bake in the oven at 200 degrees until it is golden brown.</li>
</ul>',
