                'directions_legacy' => 'Chicken:

&nbsp;
<ul>
<li>Fry the chicken in a pan with 3 tablespoons of oil. Cover them with water and add one cinnamon stick, salt and pepper. Boil them for 15 to 2o minutes; then remove the chicken and keep the chicken stock aside.</li>
<li>Later slice the chicken into small pieces.</li>
</ul>
&nbsp;

Rice:

&nbsp;
<ul>
<li>Soak the rice in water for half an hour before cooking.</li>
<li>Put the oil in a pan. Then, add the rice, chicken stock and salt. Once it starts boiling, reduce the heat &amp; cook the rice until all water evaporates.</li>
</ul>
&nbsp;

Yoghurt:

&nbsp;
<ul>
<li>In a bowl, mix the yoghurt well with the garlic, then add the salt and keep aside.</li>
</ul>
&nbsp;

Fatteh:

&nbsp;
<ul>
<li>In a pyrex place half of the bread. Then, add the rice. Next, place the chicken on top of the rice.</li>
<li>Pour yogurt on the chicken. Lastly, add the pine nuts on top. Keep the rest of the toasted bread in a bowl.</li>
<li>If you like you can add dried mint on top.</li>
</ul>',
