                'video' => 'https://youtu.be/pQSsaeGOIdo',
                'directions' => NULL,
                'ingredients' => NULL,
                'directions_legacy' => 'DOUGH

Mix the flour, baking soda, yeast, oil and mix. Gradually add the water and mix until it becomes fluffy and smooth. The dough must be soft like yogurt in consistency, add more water if necessary. 

Cover and put in a warm place for 2 hours.

Place a non-stick pan on the stove, and brush with oil.  With a small ladle, fill one small cup of coffee with the dough and spread it on a heated pan. 

Watch the bubbles form and cook only one side. When the bubbles form and the mixture start to dry, remove from pan. Repeat same procedure until all of the remaining dough is finished.

FILLING 

Mix the crushed walnuts and sugar together and then add both the blossom water.

Mix well. 

Place one teaspoon of the filling mixture into each katayef, fold over and pinch the edges well with your fingers.

Tip: add more filling to the katayef accordingly to how big the cooked dough is. 

Place the prepared Katayef on a serving plate.

SYRUP

Combine the sugar and water in a heated pan and mix until the sugar is fully dissolved. 

TIP 1: Constantly stir throughout the process to avoid any burnt residue at the bottom of the pan. Keep stirring even while 
it is boiling.  

TIP 2: Notice the syrup boiling and the water level decreasing. Turn off the stove and add the orange blossom water and lemon juice. 

Finally, pour the syrup over the Katayef only before serving 

Alternative serving option:

Put some of the prepared Katayef in a tray. Brush them with oil and bake them in the oven until crunchy. 

Once cooked soak them in the syrup for 5 minutes or pour the syrup over. 

Makes 25 pieces 
',
