                'slug' => 'kibbeh-arnabieh',
                'content' => 'One of the oldest traditional Lebanese dishes, passed on and still popular today among those who favor authenticity and traditional taste. The origin of the name comes from the use of Cauliflower previously in its making. It is also said that 7 types of different citruses contributed to its preparation. How is Sousou presenting the Kibbeh Arnabieh Recipe to you today?',
